jnxVpnMIB.name: jnxVpnMIB

revisions.description: Corrected DISPLAY-HINT for TEXTUAL-CONVENTIONs associated with a JnxVpnIdentifier.
Corrected related TEXTUAL-CONVENTIONs associated with a JnxVpnIdentifier.
A VPN MIB module that allows one to configure and monitor several types of Provider Provisioned VPNs. Initial revision.

jnxVpnMIB.contactinfo: Kireeti Kompella Postal: Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 Mathilda Ave Sunnyvale, CA 94089 Tel: +1 408 745 2000 E-mail: kireeti@juniper.net
jnxVpnMIB.description: Extended VPN MIB module to support VPN Identifier for locally switched L2 circuits.

JnxVpnType.name: JnxVpnType
JnxVpnType.description: Type of the VPN. The following types have been defined: bgpIpVpn: RFC 4364 VPNs; bgpL2Vpn: BGP-based Layer 2 VPNs (see draft-kompella-ppvpn-l2vpn); bgpVpls: BGP-based VPLS (see draft-kompella-ppvnp-vpls); l2Circuit: LDP-based point-to-point Layer 2 circuits (see RFC 4906); ldpVpls: LDP-based VPLS (see draft-lasserre-vkompella-ppvpn-vpls); opticalVpn: BGP-based Optical (port based) VPNs (see draft-ouldbrahim-bgpgmpls-ovpn); vpOxc: Virtual Private Optical Cross-Connect (see draft-ouldbrahim-ppvpn-vpoxc); ccc: proprietary Layer 2 circuit; bgpAtmVpn: ATM over MPLS (draft to be published).

JnxVpnIdentifierType.name: JnxVpnIdentifierType
JnxVpnIdentifierType.description: Type of the VPN Identifier. This includes Route Distinguishers, Route Targets, and VC IDs. none(0) This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding JnxVpnIdentifier object is a zero-length string. other(1) A VPN identifier that does not match one of the types defined in this MIB. routeDistinguisher(2) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteDistinguisher textual convention. routeDistinguisher0(3) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteDistinguisher0 textual convention. routeDistinguisher1(4) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteDistinguisher1 textual convention. routeDistinguisher2(5) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteDistinguisher2 textual convention. routeTarget(6) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteTarget textual convention. routeTarget0(7) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteTarget0 textual convention. routeTarget1(8) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteTarget1 textual convention. routeTarget2(9) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnRouteTarget2 textual convention. vcId(10) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnVCIdentifier textual convention. localSwitch(11) A VPN identifier as defined by the JnxVpnLocalSwitchIdentifier textual convention.

JnxVpnIdentifier.name: JnxVpnIdentifier
JnxVpnIdentifier.description: Syntax for a VPN identifier. A VPN Identifier is always interpreted within the context of an jnxVpnIdentifierType value. The jnxVpnIdentifierType object which defines the context must be registered immediately before the object which uses the VpnIdentifier textual convention. In other words, the object identifiers for the jnxVpnIdentifierType object and the jnxVpnIdentifier object MUST have the same length and the last sub-identifier of the jnxVpnIdentifierType object MUST be 1 less than the last sub-identifier of the jnxVpnIdentifier object.

JnxVpnVCIdentifier.name: JnxVpnVCIdentifier
JnxVpnVCIdentifier.description: Represents a PE ID, VC ID pair. The PE ID is the Router ID of the remote PE. The VC ID follows the description given in draft-martini-l2circuit-trans.

JnxVpnMultiplexor.name: JnxVpnMultiplexor
JnxVpnMultiplexor.description: Syntax for a VPN multiplexor/demultiplexor within a Pseudo-Wire Tunnel.

JnxVpnLocalSwitchIdentifier.name: JnxVpnLocalSwitchIdentifier
JnxVpnLocalSwitchIdentifier.description: The string representing the name of two interfaces that are being locally switched separated by a colon.

jnxVpnEntry.name: jnxVpnEntry
jnxVpnEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular VPN.

jnxVpnName.name: jnxVpnName
jnxVpnName.description: Name of the VPN. This should ideally be unique in the Service Provider's domain; at a minimum, it MUST be unique per Provider Edge router.

jnxVpnRowStatus.name: jnxVpnRowStatus
jnxVpnRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

jnxVpnStorageType.name: jnxVpnStorageType
jnxVpnStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

jnxVpnIdentifier.name: jnxVpnIdentifier
jnxVpnIdentifier.description: In the case of BGP VPNs, this is the Route Distinguisher for the VPN. In the case of LDP VPNs, this is the VC ID for the circuit. A value of all zeros indicates that the neither a Route Distinguisher nor a VC ID is configured for the VPN.

jnxVpnConfiguredSites.name: jnxVpnConfiguredSites
jnxVpnConfiguredSites.description: The number of sites configured in the VPN. Must be set to zero if not applicable.

jnxVpnActiveSites.name: jnxVpnActiveSites
jnxVpnActiveSites.description: The number of active sites (i.e., sites whose state is active) in the VPN.

jnxVpnLocalAddresses.name: jnxVpnLocalAddresses
jnxVpnLocalAddresses.description: The number of addresses learned from the CE device.

jnxVpnTotalAddresses.name: jnxVpnTotalAddresses
jnxVpnTotalAddresses.description: The total number of addresses in the VPN RIB.

jnxVpnAge.name: jnxVpnAge
jnxVpnAge.description: The age (i.e., time from creation till now) of this VPN in hundredths of a second.

jnxVpnIfEntry.name: jnxVpnIfEntry
jnxVpnIfEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular VPN interface.

jnxVpnIfVpnType.name: jnxVpnIfVpnType
jnxVpnIfVpnType.description: Type of the VPN to which this interface belongs.

jnxVpnIfVpnName.name: jnxVpnIfVpnName
jnxVpnIfVpnName.description: Name of the VPN to which this interface belongs.

jnxVpnIfIndex.name: jnxVpnIfIndex
jnxVpnIfIndex.description: The index of this interface in the VPN. Each interface in the VPN is given a unique index. The RowStatus says whether a given interface (i.e., a row in this table) is valid or not. Note: this index MUST NOT be zero.

jnxVpnIfRowStatus.name: jnxVpnIfRowStatus
jnxVpnIfRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

jnxVpnIfStorageType.name: jnxVpnIfStorageType
jnxVpnIfStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

jnxVpnIfAssociatedPw.name: jnxVpnIfAssociatedPw
jnxVpnIfAssociatedPw.description: Index of associated Pseudo-wire, if any, in which case the index MUST be non-zero. If none, then this index MUST be zero.

jnxVpnIfProtocol.name: jnxVpnIfProtocol
jnxVpnIfProtocol.description: Protocol running over this VPN interface. The values up to 10 are taken from draft-martini-l2circuit-trans-mpls-08.txt; the value for vpls is taken from draft-lasserre-vkompella-ppvpn-vpls-01.txt. The values from 20-23 are used when the VPN is a Layer 3 VPN.

jnxVpnIfInBandwidth.name: jnxVpnIfInBandwidth
jnxVpnIfInBandwidth.description: Maximum bandwidth that the CE connected over this VPN i/f can send to the PE, in Kilo (i.e., 1000) Bytes per second. A value of zero means there is no configured maximum.

jnxVpnIfOutBandwidth.name: jnxVpnIfOutBandwidth
jnxVpnIfOutBandwidth.description: Maximum bandwidth that the PE can send to the CE over this VPN interface, in Kilo (i.e., 1000) Bytes per second. A value of zero means there is no configured maximum.

jnxVpnPwEntry.name: jnxVpnPwEntry
jnxVpnPwEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular VPN.

jnxVpnPwVpnType.name: jnxVpnPwVpnType
jnxVpnPwVpnType.description: The type of the VPN to which this Pseudo-Wire belongs.

jnxVpnPwVpnName.name: jnxVpnPwVpnName
jnxVpnPwVpnName.description: The name of the VPN to which this Pseudo-Wire belongs.

jnxVpnPwIndex.name: jnxVpnPwIndex
jnxVpnPwIndex.description: The index of this Pseudo-Wire in the VPN. Each Pseudo Wire in the VPN is given a unique index. The RowStatus says whether a given Pseudo Wire (i.e., a row in this table) is valid or not. Note: this index MUST NOT be zero.

jnxVpnPwRowStatus.name: jnxVpnPwRowStatus
jnxVpnPwRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

jnxVpnPwStorageType.name: jnxVpnPwStorageType
jnxVpnPwStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

jnxVpnPwAssociatedInterface.name: jnxVpnPwAssociatedInterface
jnxVpnPwAssociatedInterface.description: The VPN index of the interface associated with this Pseudo Wire, if any. If there is no interface associated with this Pseudo Wire, a value of zero is to be returned.

jnxVpnPwLocalSiteId.name: jnxVpnPwLocalSiteId
jnxVpnPwLocalSiteId.description: The local site identifier for this Pseudo-Wire. If there is no local site identifier, a value of zero is to be returned.

jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteId.name: jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteId
jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteId.description: The remote site (i.e., the site at the other end of this Pseudo-Wire) identifier. If there is no remote site identifier, a value of zero is to be returned.

jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddrType.name: jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddrType
jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddrType.description: The type of address assigned to the remote PE.

jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddress.name: jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddress
jnxVpnRemotePeIdAddress.description: The address of the remote PE, i.e., the router at the other end of the Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwTunnelType.name: jnxVpnPwTunnelType
jnxVpnPwTunnelType.description: The type of the tunnel over which the Pseudo-Wire is carried. If several Pseudo-Wires can be carried in one tunnel, each Pseudo-Wire is identified by the multiplexor/ demultiplexor within this tunnel.

jnxVpnPwTunnelName.name: jnxVpnPwTunnelName
jnxVpnPwTunnelName.description: The name of the Tunnel over which this Pseudo-Wire is carried, if any.

jnxVpnPwReceiveDemux.name: jnxVpnPwReceiveDemux
jnxVpnPwReceiveDemux.description: The value of the demultiplexor that identifies received packets as belonging to this Pseudo-Wire, if any.

jnxVpnPwTransmitDemux.name: jnxVpnPwTransmitDemux
jnxVpnPwTransmitDemux.description: The value of the demultiplexor that identifies transmitted packets as belonging to this Pseudo-Wire, if any.

jnxVpnPwTunnelStatus.name: jnxVpnPwTunnelStatus
jnxVpnPwTunnelStatus.description: Status of the PE-to-PE tunnel over which the Pseudo- Wire is carried.

jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteStatus.name: jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteStatus
jnxVpnPwRemoteSiteStatus.description: Status of the interface at the remote end of the Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwTimeUp.name: jnxVpnPwTimeUp
jnxVpnPwTimeUp.description: The total time in hundredths of a second that this Pseudo-Wire has been operational.

jnxVpnPwTransitions.name: jnxVpnPwTransitions
jnxVpnPwTransitions.description: The number of state transitions (up -> down and down -> up) this Tunnel has undergone.

jnxVpnPwLastTransition.name: jnxVpnPwLastTransition
jnxVpnPwLastTransition.description: The time in hundredths of a second since the last transition occurred on this Tunnel.

jnxVpnPwPacketsSent.name: jnxVpnPwPacketsSent
jnxVpnPwPacketsSent.description: The number of packets that have been sent over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwOctetsSent.name: jnxVpnPwOctetsSent
jnxVpnPwOctetsSent.description: The number of octets that have been sent over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwPacketsReceived.name: jnxVpnPwPacketsReceived
jnxVpnPwPacketsReceived.description: The number of packets that have been received over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwOctetsReceived.name: jnxVpnPwOctetsReceived
jnxVpnPwOctetsReceived.description: The number of octets that have been received over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwLRPacketsSent.name: jnxVpnPwLRPacketsSent
jnxVpnPwLRPacketsSent.description: The number of packets that have been sent over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwLROctetsSent.name: jnxVpnPwLROctetsSent
jnxVpnPwLROctetsSent.description: The number of octets that have been sent over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwLRPacketsReceived.name: jnxVpnPwLRPacketsReceived
jnxVpnPwLRPacketsReceived.description: The number of packets that have been received over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnPwLROctetsReceived.name: jnxVpnPwLROctetsReceived
jnxVpnPwLROctetsReceived.description: The number of octets that have been received over this Pseudo-Wire.

jnxVpnRTTable.name: jnxVpnRTTable
jnxVpnRTTable.description: Table of Route Targets for a VPN.

jnxVpnRTEntry.name: jnxVpnRTEntry
jnxVpnRTEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular VPN.

jnxVpnRTVpnType.name: jnxVpnRTVpnType
jnxVpnRTVpnType.description: The type of the VPN for which this list of Route Targets are defined.

jnxVpnRTVpnName.name: jnxVpnRTVpnName
jnxVpnRTVpnName.description: The name of the VPN for which this list of Route Targets are defined.

jnxVpnRTIndex.name: jnxVpnRTIndex
jnxVpnRTIndex.description: The index within the list of Route Targets that specifies individual Route Targets that define the VPN. Note: this index MUST NOT be zero.

jnxVpnRTRowStatus.name: jnxVpnRTRowStatus
jnxVpnRTRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

jnxVpnRTStorageType.name: jnxVpnRTStorageType
jnxVpnRTStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

jnxVpnRTType.name: jnxVpnRTType
jnxVpnRTType.description: Type of the following Route Target. This can one of 'routeTarget[012]' or 'none'.

jnxVpnRT.name: jnxVpnRT
jnxVpnRT.description: Route Target for the VPN. If the jnxVpnRTType is 'none', this value should be all zeros.

jnxVpnRTFunction.name: jnxVpnRTFunction
jnxVpnRTFunction.description: The route target export distribution type.

jnxVpnIfUp.name: jnxVpnIfUp
jnxVpnIfUp.description: A jnxVpnIfUp notification is generated when the interface with index jnxVpnIfIndex belonging to the VPN named jnxVpnIfVpnName of type jnxVpnIfVpnType transitions out of the 'down' state.

jnxVpnIfDown.name: jnxVpnIfDown
jnxVpnIfDown.description: A jnxVpnIfDown notification is generated when the interface with index jnxVpnIfIndex belonging to the VPN named jnxVpnIfVpnName of type jnxVpnIfVpnType transitions to the 'down' state.

jnxVpnPwUp.name: jnxVpnPwUp
jnxVpnPwUp.description: A jnxVpnPwUp notification is generated when the Pseudo-Wire with index jnxVpnPwIndex belonging to the VPN named jnxVpnPwVpnName of type jnxVpnPwVpnType transitions out of the 'down' state.

jnxVpnPwDown.name: jnxVpnPwDown
jnxVpnPwDown.description: A jnxVpnPwDown notification is generated when the Pseudo-Wire with index jnxVpnPwIndex belonging to the VPN named jnxVpnPwVpnName of type jnxVpnPwVpnType transitions to the 'down' state.
